{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox video game | title = Amy | image = Amy game cover.png | developer = [[VectorCell]] | publisher = Lexis Numérique | director = [[Paul Cuisset]] | producer = | designer = | programmer = | artist = | writer = | composer = | engine = [[PhyreEngine]] | platforms = [[Xbox 360]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Gilbert |first=Ben |date=22 June 2011 |url=https://www.engadget.com/2011/06/22/amy-dev-paul-cuisset-discusses-games-autistic-character-fema/ |title='Amy' dev Paul Cuisset discusses game's autistic character, female leads |website=[[Engadget]] ([[Joystiq]]) |publisher=[[Oath Inc.]] |accessdate=20 April 2018}}</ref> [[PlayStation 3]]<ref name="Lexis Numerique Press Release"/> | released = {{vgrelease|WW|11 January 2012|NA|11 January 2012 <small>(PS3)</small>}} | genre = [[Survival horror]], [[Stealth game|stealth]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] }}
'''''Amy''''' is a [[survival horror]] [[stealth game|stealth]] video game, released in 2012, developed by [[VectorCell]] and published by Lexis Numérique. ''Amy'' depicts the journey of Amy, an [[Autism|autistic]] [[psychic]] child, and her protector Lana. In a city suffused with a [[zombie]]-type infection which Amy is immune to (and can heal Lana from), Lana must stay near her young charge, for frequent healing, while protecting her from the infected, and the Phoenix Foundation who hopes to exploit her. ''Amy'' received [[List of video games notable for negative reception|negative critical reviews]], although updates were released to address complaints.
==Gameplay== The player controls Lana, the woman escorting Amy and protecting her as the two attempt to escape their disease-ridden town. They encounter monsters and the military, among other foes, in their attempt to escape.<ref name="Lexis Numerique Press Release" /> The player is forced to protect Amy from the zombies, often making her hide, to avoid detection. However, Lana starts succumbing to the plague without medicine, and thus must remain close to Amy, to return for healing. There are syringes infrequently, which allow Lana to heal without returning to Amy. However, when Lana is somewhat infected, she can safely walk past zombies, which necessitates a balance between healing and zombification. At certain times, Lana must rely on Amy for other abilities: Amy can use shockwaves, to push enemies and objects, causing distractions, as well as a sound bubble, muffling glass either being smashed or stepped on, defending Lana. Amy also hacks computers and climbs through vents when Lana needs her to.
==Plot== The player must escort Amy, an autistic 8-year-old as they try to get her out of a city overrun with wild creatures and enemies. Lana (Sabine Crossen) and Amy are traveling to a doctor in Silver City via train, when an explosion derails the train, and their plans. They discover that the people have been turned to monsters via a strange infection, and must escape the monsters, as they continue their journey to the city. They must also fend off the Phoenix Foundation, an organisation who intends to control Amy and exploit her strange powers.<ref name="Lexis Numerique Press Release">{{cite web |url=http://www.lexis-games.com/wp-content/uploads/Lexis_GDC-2011_Lineup_Alert_V0.pdf |title=The French Studio Lexis Numerique Announces Lineup and New Assets for Game Developers Conference 2011 |website=Lexis Numérique |accessdate=5 May 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021173557/http://www.lexis-games.com/wp-content/uploads/Lexis_GDC-2011_Lineup_Alert_V0.pdf |archivedate=21 October 2012 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lexis-numerique.fr/category/amy-en/ |title=Lexis Numérique announces new lineup at GDC 2011 |website=Lexis Numérique |accessdate=5 May 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223100126/http://www.lexis-numerique.fr/category/amy-en/ |archivedate=23 February 2014 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>
==Development== On 3 April 2012, VectorCell announced a patch for ''Amy'' on the game's official [[Facebook]] page. The patch was released on 6 April. Major changes include the saving of the player's progress during chapters, the addition of more checkpoints, skipping of sequences in-game and several corrections to the subtitles.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2012-04-11-panned-survival-horror-amy-receives-major-update|title=Panned survival horror Amy receives major update|work=Eurogamer.net|access-date=2018-06-19|language=en}}</ref>
{{clear}}
