''Amy'' received "generally unfavorable reviews" on both platforms according to the [[Review aggregator|review aggregation]] website [[Metacritic]].<ref name="MCPS3"/><ref name="MCX360"/> [[IGN]]'s Colin Moriarty stated at the end of his review that he "spent at least a dozen hours with [''Amy''], got as far as the end portion of the fifth chapter, and gave up out of sheer anger and frustration."<ref name="IGN"/> ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Jeff Cork stated that "as a downloadable title, I wasn't expecting [''Amy''] to measure up against the triple-A juggernauts of the survival horror genre. However, I was expecting a game that was at least playable and contained some kind of entertainment. Make no mistake: Whether [''Amy''] is delivered to you via download, retail SKU, direct brain wave, or retinal implant, it is terrible and should be avoided."<ref name="GI"/> Jim Sterling of ''[[Destructoid]]'' went as far in his review as to describe ''Amy'' as "one of the worst games ever made".<ref name="Destruct"/> [[Ben "Yahtzee" Croshaw]] of ''[[The Escapist (magazine)|The Escapist]]'' criticized the game's awkward camera views, poor optimization to Xbox, and also gave up the game in frustration due to the addition of poorly implemented stealth mechanics, and later stated that it was the worst game of 2012.<ref>{{cite web |author=Escapist |date=8 August 2012 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ehcU90xJrwE |title=AMY (Zero Punctuation) |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Alphabet Inc.]] |accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Escapist |date=9 January 2013 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6V6MI1ZSRfg |title=TOP 5 GAMES OF 2012 (Zero Punctuation) |website=YouTube |publisher=Alphabet Inc. |accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref> The most positive PlayStation 3 review was given by Thomas Pichler from ''GamingXP''. He praised the main protagonist, but criticized the periodical lack of explanation of what to do next.<ref>{{cite web |last=Pichler |first=Thomas |date=1 October 2012 |url=http://www.gamingxp.com/bericht-5380-sony_computer_entertainment-vector_unit_inc.-ps3-amy.htm |title=Amy PS3 Review |language=German |website=GamingXP |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113190222/http://www.gamingxp.com/bericht-5380-sony_computer_entertainment-vector_unit_inc.-ps3-amy.htm |archivedate=13 January 2012 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> Alan Bradley of [[GamesRadar+]] said ''Amy'' was boring and no fun to play and really unpleasant for most of the time. He also criticised the combination of a bad control system and widely spaced checkpoints that meant the player would have to repeat sections numerous times.<ref name=GamesRadarRev>{{cite web |last=Bradley |first=Adam |date=13 January 2012 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/amy-review/ |title=AMY review (X360) |website=[[GamesRadar+]] |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref>
411Mania gave the Xbox 360 version a score of 3.3 out of 10 and said that it "tries to offer something new. The good news is that it does introduce some new gameplay concepts that can be toyed with by developers. The bad news, the controls and gameplay are implemented in such a way the game will just leave you frustrated and angry."<ref>{{cite web |last=Vote |first=Todd |date=17 January 2012 |url=http://www.411mania.com/games/downloadable_content/219806/Amy-(Xbox-Live-Arcade)-Review.htm |title=Amy (Xbox Live Arcade) Review |website=411Mania |accessdate=20 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512093256/http://www.411mania.com/games/downloadable_content/219806/Amy-(Xbox-Live-Arcade)-Review.htm |archivedate=12 May 2012 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> Susan Arendt of ''The Escapist'' gave the same console version one-and-a-half stars out of five and stated, "Pick something to hate about videogames, and ''Amy'' has it. Graphics glitches, lousy design, repetitious gameplay, mushy controls, bad acting, horrible save system ... it's all there. The game's few good ideas simply aren't enough to suffer through the amount of crap surrounding them."<ref name="Escapist"/> ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' gave the same console version a D, saying, "Oddly, it is tempting to look forward to a second outing, however unlikely. Because videogame disasters this gruesome are fascinating. And, to be dangerously optimistic, ''Amy'' can't get much worse."<ref>{{cite web |last=Mastrapa |first=Gus |date=23 January 2012 |url=https://games.avclub.com/amy-1798229403 |title=Amy (X360) |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |publisher=[[The Onion]] |accessdate=20 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125073618/http://www.avclub.com/articles/amy,68014/ |archivedate=25 January 2012 |deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro UK]]'' gave the same console version one out of ten, saying, "Awful in almost every possible aspect, this hugely disappointing download is not just a failure as a survival horror but as a video game."<ref name="Metro"/> ''The Digital Fix'' gave the PlayStation 3 version a score of one out of ten, saying, "If you need to satiate your survival-horror appetite go revisit the ''Resident Evil'' series, ''Clock Tower'' or ''Parasite Eve'' as you will get much more interesting and developed games despite them being released over a decade ago."<ref>{{cite web |last=Gallagher |first=Gareth |date=17 January 2012 |url=https://www.thedigitalfix.com/gaming/content/578/amy/ |title=Amy Review (PS3) |website=The Digital Fix |publisher=Poisonous Monkey |accessdate=20 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150110043707/http://gaming.thedigitalfix.com/content/id/578/amy.html |archivedate=10 January 2015 |deadurl=no}}</ref>
It was included among the worst games of all time by GamesRadar+ in 2014<ref>{{cite web |author=GamesRadar staff |date=27 June 2014 |url=http://www.gamesradar.com/worst-games-all-time/ |title=The 100 worst games of all time |website=GamesRadar+ |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=20 April 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509133313/http://www.gamesradar.com/worst-games-all-time/ |archivedate=9 May 2015 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> and in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |author=GamesRadar staff |date=9 August 2017 |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/worst-games-all-time/3/ |title=The 50 worst games of all time (Page 3) |website=GamesRadar+ |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=20 April 2018}}</ref>
