The '''Rungra People's Pleasure Ground''' is an [[amusement park]] located in [[Rŭngrado|Rungra Island]], [[Pyongyang]], [[North Korea]]. It was opened in 2012 in a ceremony with [[Kim Jong-un|Kim Jong Un]] and his wife [[Ri Sol-ju]].<ref name=Huffington>{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Sam|title=North Korea's Kim Jong Un Shows Off New Wife Ri Sol Ju|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/26/kim-jong-un-wife_n_1705130.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=1 November 2012|date=26 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{youtube|g0ZbzSkoYQI|KCTV (Kim Jong Un and his wife Ri Sol Ju Visits Rungna People′s Pleasure Ground)}} {{dead link|date=January 2016}}</ref> It has a dolphinarium, swimming pool, and a mini golf course.

